{
  "texts": [
    "Performance of OPT modelsWhen analyzing the OPT models (1.3B, 2.7B and 6.7B), we are looking at a smaller range of parameter sizes compared to the larger Llama 2 models (7B, 13B and 70B).",
    "Within this more modest model size range of the OPT models, performance improvements are relatively gradual, especially between the 1.3B and 2.7B models, where both BERTScore and BLEU metrics show minor differences.",
    "This suggests that in these smaller models, increasing the parameter size from 1.3B to 2.7B offers little advantage in terms of fluency or semantic alignment.",
    "However, the 6.7B model shows a more substantial improvement, particularly in BLEU scores, indicating that this model benefits more from its increased capacity.",
    "The performance shift from 2.7B to 6.7B is more pronounced than from 1.3B to 2.7B, suggesting that the gains from scaling model size become more apparent only at higher parameters within this range."
  ]
}